The 27-year-old former Kings player joins the Port Elizabeth based side on a short-term loan. CAPE TOWN - Worcester Warriors utility back Scott van Breda has joined the Southern Kings squad on loan for the remainder of their European tour. The 27-year-old former Kings player joins the Port Elizabeth based side on a short-term loan. Van Breda has joined the team for the remaining two tour matches. He played for Western Province, Stormers and the Jersey Reds. The Kings will this week face Glasgow Warriors on Friday at Scotstoun Stadium, Glasgow. The South African side has lost four PRO14 matches so far. 